body:
The Social Gaze was a Spring 2016 program that explored the intersections of cinematic sociology, improvisational performance, and creative writing.  

Students in The Social Gaze have developed partially scripted, partially improvised short performances to explore issues of identity, ideology, and social theory using a dynamic quarter-long creative process of character development, research, and performance practice.

body:

title: Media Artists Studio Film Screening
body:
Media Artists Studio is a year long program for advanced student media makers that looks deeply into the medium while producing individual projects that push conventional media boundaries.

Come to the film screening to watch 14 premiers that include music videos, experimental documentaries, animation, narratives, and more.

This year's MAS portfolio is inspired by transmasculinity, our historical and societal urge to "fix" non-issues (autism, sexuality), the European witch-hunts, extravagant possibilities for an empowering experience at a woman's clinic, the spaces we occupy when we let ourselves daydream, and more thought-provoking work!

Warning: mature content, strong language, and strobe effects.

title: Memory Vessels: A Ceramic Exploration Through Presence With Experience
body:
This collective show brings together a body of work that illustrates the dynamic possibilities of ceramics as medium.

June 9th: 4p-8p, June 10th: 10a-7p, June 11th: 10a-4p

 

Forms and intentions have co-emerged here.

Jesse Dotson

Recontextualizes a pictographic language

Kristeen Anderson 

Creates artifacts of deep memory

Val Shamma 

Re-evaluates technological transmutation

Ian Hazard-Bill

Explores cultural and personal reciprocation

Jasmine Olson 

Translates nature’s sublimity through abstract form

 

They should not be understood as wholly isolated from each other, it is in the intersections of their relationships that one can examine what they collectively offer.

title: Student Art Gallery Show Opening: a Queer, Feminist Exhibition of Multimedia Works and Performance
body:
I've Written a Letter to Daddy is a solo exhibition of multimedia works and performance by India Elizabeth Davidson. The opening is on Thursday, June 9th from 5-7pm with refreshments and a performance piece. The show focuses upon the place of sexual desire and its expression in an evolving society, who determines what is deemed “acceptable”, and how they do so. Further explored is the effect of this upon the queer experience, in conjunction with the cultural co-option, commodification of, and violence against the female gendered body.

https://www.facebook.com/events/1098854953513877/

title: Library Closed; Library Building Open Normal Hours
body: The Library is closed Aug 30 and 31 for a staff retreat. Borrowers can return books, DVDs, etc in the afterhours collection bins outside the Red Square entrance to the building. Media Loan is closed and no media items can be returned on these days. The Writing Center will offer a table to support student writers in the Library Lobby. The QuaSR is closed, as is the Evergreen Gallery, the Archives, and all services inside the Library proper.

title: Student Group Registration Workshop
body:
Student Activities presents: Getting Started Workshop

looking to start a Student Group? attend this 2-hour workshop that provides the essentials for organizing a student group.

basic step-by-step:

  1. have an idea for your student group
  2. seen an advisor in the Student Activities office, CAB 313
  3. get 4 people (including you) to form the group
  4. sign up for a registration workshop
  5. go to the workshop!

 

http://www.evergreen.edu/activities/home.htm

title: State of Washington Legislative Internship Program - Priority Application Deadline
body:
Priority Application Deadline - Monday, October 10, 2016 @ 11:59 pm

Students will work as an intern with a legislator and her or his staff for a regular forty-hour work week during the 2017 legislative session (The 2017 legislative session will extend over both winter and spring quarters). Intensive staff-apprenticeship activities include conducting legislative research, drafting policy and other documents, bill tracking, and constituent communications. Responsibilities also include attendance at guest presentations, seminars, workshops on budget, and media panels.

Evergreen students accepted as legislative interns will develop an internship learning contract profiling legislative responsibilities and linkages to their academic development.  

http://www.evergreen.edu/catalog/2016-17/programs/washingtonstatelegislativeinternships-14796

http://leg.wa.gov/Internships/Pages/default.aspx

title: Transfer Day
body:
If you are a new transfer student joining us this fall please consider attending Transfer Day on Wednesday, May 17, 2017.  This is an excellent opportunity to prepare for registration, learn about academic life, and connect with campus services designed to support you in your success at Evergreen. 

  • Schedule
repeat: Wednesday, May 17, 2017 - 9:00 am to 12:00 pm

title: All-Campus Mentoring Day
body:
Develop a vision and a map for your pathway through Evergreen. Plan for graduate school. Get the tools you need to start crafting your future now.

  • Schedule
repeat: Wednesday, May 17, 2017 - 1:00 pm to 4:00 pm

title: Academic Fair
body: Before registration, faculty gather in a common space to answer your questions and distribute materials for their upcoming program or course for Summer 2017 and Fall 2017.
repeat: Wednesday, May 17, 2017 - 4:00 pm to 6:00 pm

title: Annual Academic Statement Deadline
body: Annual Academic Statement submission window ends.
repeat: Thursday, May 18, 2017 (All day)

title: Open Registration for Fall 2017
body:
• Seniors: Monday, May 22 (also: Tacoma, Tribal, and graduate students)
  • Juniors: Tuesday, May 23
  • Sophomores: Wednesday, May 24
  • Freshmen: Thursday, May 25

Check my.evergreen.edu for your class standing, time ticket and other information.

Incoming freshmen can also register for 16-credit programs May 8-17.
repeat: Monday, May 22, 2017 (All day)

title: Open Registration for Summer 2017
body:
• Seniors: Monday, May 22 (also: Tacoma, Tribal, and graduate students)
  • Juniors: Tuesday, May 23
  • Sophomores: Wednesday, May 24
  • Freshmen: Thursday, May 25

Check my.evergreen.edu for your class standing, time ticket and other information.

Non-enrolled (special) students may register beginning Monday May 29.

Students using Evergreen employee tuition waivers must register in person beginning July 3. Since summer is self-sustaining, there are no tuition waivers in summer for students that are Washington state employees, 60+, or National Guard.
repeat: Monday, May 22, 2017 (All day)
